What Does a Newborn Baby Boy Wear?

A newborn baby typically wears soft and comfortable clothing such as 1-piece bodysuits, matching tops and bottoms and socks to keep his feet warm. These clothes are designed to be easy to put on and take off, and they often snap or zip for convenience. Keep layering options like sweaters close by for newborns and you’ll be ready for whatever the weather throws at you. Don’t forget to accessorize your baby’s daily outfits with hats, socks and mittens to keep him cozy and snuggly-soft.

Popular Baby Boy Clothes Trends

Cute animal prints and patterns on rompers or coordinating sets are a popular choice for baby boys. Neutral colors like gray, beige and white are timeless and versatile. And parents are prioritizing organic, eco-friendly fabrics more and more for their little ones. But let’s face it, babies look adorable in so many things. Let your imagination run wild when building up your baby boy’s wardrobe.

How Long Do Babies Wear Newborn Clothes?

Babies typically wear newborn size clothes for the first few weeks to a few months, depending on their size and how fast they grow. It is important to keep in mind that every baby is different and may outgrow newborn-sized clothing at different rates. When in doubt, it’s important to size up as newborn babies can outgrow clothes quickly.

Baby Outfits Made Easy

The quickest and easiest way to dress a baby is to have pre-coordinated baby clothing sets and multipacks. These items come already paired together and are ready to wear, saving you time. With matching sets, you can easily dress your baby in coordinated outfits without having to spend time and effort mixing and matching individual pieces. With multipacks of bodysuits, pants and more, you can stock up easily and save. Stress less knowing you already have clean and matching clothing options readily available for your little ones.
